Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat(dream): cold-tier memory recall surfaces archived
 rules on relevant prompts (#2746)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

PR1 (#2723) archived the lowest-signal memories — ~130 BINDING/Non-Negotiable
rules of a ~693-entry corpus — out of the session-loaded hot MEMORY.md into a
NOT-loaded cold MEMORY_ARCHIVE.md, so those rules stopped influencing behaviour.
RECALL closes that gap: when the prompt is topically relevant to a cold rule,
surface it for that one turn.

- recall.py: DB-free, stdlib-only pure scoring core (RecallHit,
  recall_cold_memory, render_recall_block). Tokenizes the prompt (ambient
  system-reminder/command blocks stripped first so injected MEMORY.md text
  cannot self-match), scores each cold-index entry, applies a 2-match relevance
  floor before any BINDING(+3)/user_(+2) boost, dedupes against the hot index
  (pointer name + renamed-file signature-substring guard), ranks, and caps to
  5 hits / 1500 bytes / 200 chars-per-line. Reuses decay/reindex filename
  constants as the stable contract.
- memory_recall.py: thin UserPromptSubmit hook leaf; resolves the project memory
  dir (transcript sibling memory dir, else the cwd-slug project dir), imports the
  core without django.setup(), prints the block. Registered LAST in the
  hook_router UserPromptSubmit chain. Crash-proof and silent on degrade.
- teatree_settings.py: extracted _teatree_bool_setting out of hook_router (now a
  shared leaf both import) so the leaf reads its kill-switch without a
  hook_router-leaf cycle; hook_router nets -22 LOC (shrink-only ratchet).
- memory management command (memory recall) + DJANGO_GROUPS entry
  (core_dispatch); off-switch memory_recall_enabled (default TRUE) +
  gate memory-recall disable/enable/status self-rescue.
- nit-4 (#2723 review): reindex.signature_text — one frontmatter-aware,
  description-preferring, uncapped extractor now shared by the hot index,
  gates._signature_line (cold index), and the retention probe, fixing the weak
  node-type signature; _summary_for delegates to it then clips.
- nit-3 (#2723 review): byte-budget archival integration test exercising the
  multibyte-only byte branch of the decay budget tier.

Docs regenerated (cli-reference, management-commands).
